Squizzy::

She leaned back and tried to relax. But she couldn't help but feel 
uneasy at all this.  Why did he darken up the windows, was so she 
could see where she was going, she thought. She wondered why he 
wouldn't answer her questions.  She leaned back, but he arrow hit the 
seat.  She groaned a little and then asked, "Will you at least tell 
me your name?"  she swallowed hard and tried to make her voice sound 
a little more calm, "Please?"



--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, Yanshosh@a... wrote:
> ::Dark One::
> 
> "I'm afraid I can't let you out," says Dark One, still over his 
intercom, 
> "You won't make it very far on your own anyhow."
> 
> He pauses for a while, leaving most of her questions unanswered as 
the window 
> she had been looking out of darkened and finally went completely 
black. "Rest 
> for now. We'll arrive shortly."
